description: From Latin sejunctio. See sejoin, sejunct.

entries.meaning: (obsolete) The act of disjoining, or the state of being disjoined.
examples: The constitution of that people was made by a sejunction and separation of them from all other nations on the earth: and this began in Abraham  [â€¦]

entries.meaning: (psychology) An interruption of the continuity of association-complexes which leads to a breaking up of the personality.
